  "texts": [
    "The straightforward nature of blockchains implies such irregular values can be unsurprising or controlled by aggressors.",
    "An erratic state (energetic libraries) happens when savvy contracts stack outside library code or join third-party usefulness through interfacing like delegate calls or work calls to outside contracts.",
    "As this makes contract behavior subordinate to outside untrusted code, assailants misuse such associations.",
    "For illustration, consider a contract that depends on an outside Prophet library for sourcing basic information like resource costs.",
    "An assailant can send a noxious adaptation of this library with inaccurate information to seize the target contract's state."
